<br>
The current Good vs. Evil thing is so utterly simplistic that it's almost juvenile.  Yes, there's some mature content, but for the most part Everquest is PG-rated.  Hence, going for the lowest common denominator (as must be done in any successful MMO game, IMO) means going for the easiest definition.  So I doubt it'll change.<br>
<br>
But the race war servers bring up a good point - if a dwarf can fight at the side of a high elf, is it *that* much of a stretch to have them fighting at the side of anyone else?  Of course, letting this happen more or less opens a floodgate, and soon you have people of all kinds grouping up regardless of alignment - e.g. what we have now.<br>
<br>
It's kind of a kuldge, but one I could live with.  I'd really like to see a somewhat more mature definition of alignments than good and evil.  Even law vs. chaos was in D&D, and while it, too, isn't perfect, it's a lot more accurate than the former.  But this is EQ and good vs. evil is built right into the game; oh well.  I guess I'm hoping for too much. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/01 7:05:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2155.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is there still hope?  Quasi RP server on Flameplay</span><hr size=1> Diety Based Team PvP will get you roleplay.  All you need to do is, decide on how to divide the dieties and the number of teams.<br>
