---<br>
Natuarally, the table or rewards/transgressions/factions in relation to standings of other players would become complex, and prone to abuse like:<br>
<br>
"That moron Challenger was again killing his other-account SK whole night long with macro keys, and now is again neutral standing. Grrr...."<br>
<br>
Similar thingies were implemented in UO, and that was FUN!<br>
<br>
UO anecdote: I remember when we got attacked by vile murderer (sorta standing of a player, denoted red for this) that quickly dispatched our overloaded, tired, unarmed miner characters (one used to mine rare secretive colored ore strains in remote caves). Then my ghost followed him through the portal he created and watched where he hauled the piles of our precious, stolen ore. Next we got 4-5 friends, layed an ambush and killed the guy even on the stairs of his home so he had no time to lock it - we could plunder back all his possesions. He was still whining as to how he lost 15% of his battle stats - which was the penalty for a vile murderer once he got PvP executed. Still, evil players were accepting this risk and punishment for the fear and benefits of their 'profession'.<br>
<br>
To reach the balance here, is extremely tuff.<br>
But the game engine of EQ is all set in place and it takes just a little imagination, creativity and will to do it. Even more, Ralf Koster (Designer Dragon) that worked on this heavy concepts before in UO is already a team member in Verant (although working on the Star Wars side now ehh)...<br>
