</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uraxee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raxee</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/01 5:50:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2155.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.crosswinds.net/~iftavedarx/raxee2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is there still hope?  Quasi RP server on Flameplay</span><hr size=1> RP elitists don't last long.  They tend to sneer and whatnot at the people who do anything other than RP, you know, the ones who do stuff like hunt, gain levels, and occasionally trade, etc.  However, they soon 'grow frustrated' and 'quit due to a game that claims to be a role-playing game, but simply doesn't support it'.  And so on.<br>
<br>
Even on an RP server there will be lots of non-RP stuff.  But that's EQ.  RP is one aspect of it, one you can ignore.<br>
<br>
The reason I'm looking forward to it is I know lots of people with RP potential will come to this server.  Even if lots of people come because they don't like farming, lots of true newbies show up - the server will be green and all - and what have you, there still will be a larger number of RPers than before.<br>
<br>
Coordinating such an enormous RP community is a task I do not envy anyone.  With that large a potential number of RPers, there's quite a possibility of total chaos, nobody knowing what everyone else is doing or wants.  But I'm sure it would work out, somehow, if people are willing to try it out.  There are plenty of potential solutions.<br>
<br>
I've been in a fair-sized EQ RP community for a while.  We've had elitists, we've had bad RPers, we've had RPers that take WAAAAY too many liberties in the GM-less RP system EQ uses, we've had ones that I vehemently dislike in an OOC context, we've had ones whom everybody hated both in and out of character, and all that.  But it's still been good.<br>
<br>
The aggregate still works out for the best.  The large number of RPers who stick around are responsible enough to enjoy the game and let others do it too.  The rest do one of two things; either they quit RP entirely (and blame something like the game or other RPers) or they join a guild of like players.  Just avoid said guild in the second case.<br>
<br>
Of course, this is all pending that this server actually comes into existence.  It may not happen.  Brad only said they were considering it. <p>Raxee L'Noamuth, 46th season Roguess of Old Fennin</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc>News Bulletin</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
